WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.690 --> 00:00:06.550
 [Ganges] 

00:00:14.980 --> 00:00:23.000
 [The Ganges River travels 2500 km of plains in northern India before emptying into the Bay of Bengal] 

00:00:24.090 --> 00:00:27.000
 [Its basin crosses 11 states] 

00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:34.430
 [The Ganges basin in India covers an area of ​​860,000 km2] 

00:00:36.430 --> 00:00:43.000
 [It is the largest and most populated basin in the world, with more than 600 million inhabitants in India alone] 

00:00:43.830 --> 00:00:49.380
 [The river is a religious symbol and gives economic support to hundreds of millions of Indians] 

00:00:51.750 --> 00:00:56.190
 [The Ganges is venerated as a divinity by Hindus] 

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:02.080
 For us, the Ganges is a spiritual river. 

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:04.710
 There are people who bathe 

00:01:04.710 --> 00:01:06.710
 usually in the Ganges. 

00:01:06.710 --> 00:01:08.860
 For them, the Ganges is a way of life. 

00:01:19.310 --> 00:01:22.910
 [The Ganges provides water that is used for] 

00:01:22.910 --> 00:01:28.910
 [water, take baths, drink, generate hydroelectric energy and as a means of navigation] 

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:37.530
 [At present, pollution pollutes the sacred waters of the Ganges] 

00:01:41.880 --> 00:01:47.880
 [A growing population, together with rapid urbanization and industrialization - inadequately planned - add to the burden of pollutants] 

00:01:50.780 --> 00:01:53.060
 I used to fish a good amount of fish. 

00:01:53.060 --> 00:01:57.180
 Since the river is polluted, the fish die. 

00:01:58.670 --> 00:02:03.550
 [Fifty large cities and hundreds of smaller towns and villages pour sewage and solid waste into the river] 

00:02:06.280 --> 00:02:12.280
 [More than 3 billion liters of wastewater, mostly untreated, flows into the river every day] 

00:02:14.360 --> 00:02:18.790
 [Most cities do not have sewers and even where they exist, less than half of the wastewater is untreated] 

00:02:18.790 --> 00:02:24.790
 [because cities do not have money to build treatment plants or lack the technical knowledge to make them work efficiently] 

00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:33.600
 [Trash litters the streets and is taken to the river] 

00:02:54.940 --> 00:02:58.900
 [764 industries pollute the affluent with 500 million liters of sewage and hazardous chemicals on a daily basis] 

00:02:58.900 --> 00:03:04.380
 [Paper and pulp industries, textiles, sugar and leather] 

00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:14.000
 [764 industries pollute the river with 500 million liters of sewage and hazardous chemicals on a daily basis] 

00:03:14.220 --> 00:03:18.000
 [This affects the health and livelihoods of people living on its banks] 

00:03:19.690 --> 00:03:23.000
 [This damages the aquatic health of the river] 

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:27.670
 My family has worked 

00:03:27.670 --> 00:03:32.210
 in the fields for years. 

00:03:32.210 --> 00:03:36.050
 Since we started receiving water from the tanneries to water our fields, 

00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:40.200
 the plants are ruined due to the high content of chromium and other salts in the water. 

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:49.140
 The Ganges Clean Mission of the Government of India aims to recover the symbolic river. 

00:03:51.550 --> 00:03:53.550
 [Recovery plan] 

00:03:53.550 --> 00:03:59.000
 [Treat domestic sewage, control industrial pollution, stop the dumping of solid waste] 

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.510
 [improve the banks, increase knowledge about the river] 

00:04:04.510 --> 00:04:06.510
 [develop top-tier institutions to recover the Ganges] 

00:04:06.510 --> 00:04:08.510
 [Work in progress] 

00:04:08.510 --> 00:04:11.000
 [2000 km of sewers, 300 mld of new wastewater treatment capacity] 

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.910
 [100 modern water quality monitoring stations] 

00:04:13.910 --> 00:04:16.000
 [The World Bank supports the Ganges Clean Mission with a loan of US $ 1 billion] 

